The new vaccine
Free vaccinations for children born in August
From January onwards, children born on or after August 2 of last year will be able to receive the pneumococcal vaccine free of charge.
The condition is that you have not received a single dose of the vaccine before.
Those who started the vaccine last year or earlier have to cover other doses of the vaccine as well.
The first dose of the vaccine must be received between the third and fifth months of a child's age.
Last year, one-quarter of families voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal disease.
The parents however paid for a dose 1600 crowns and more.
Four doses are needed to vaccinate younger children.
Generally, experts estimate that insurance companies will spend 300,000 to 450,000 crowns annually on vaccines.
However, they will save on treatment, which is needed for unvaccinated children.
So far the state has spent about 500,000 children annually on all vaccinations.
Covered vaccination was initiated by the so-called Janota package.
Pneumococcal is the cause of otitis media, but also of serious infections including meningitis and sepsis.
According to hospital research, 28 children under 10 years of age die from pneumococcal infections in our country every year.
In addition to the Czech Republic, pneumococcal vaccine coverage in children was introduced in approximately 40 countries.
Will the vaccine be compulsory?
However, at the same time there are opinions, that this vaccine could be mandatory in the future.
From January it must be covered by the insurance companies and volunteer.
