Instead, with the support of the latest computer tools it would be a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and solutions for claims assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information provided by manufacturers, then elaborating it and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the American group Solera, is the leading firm; 80% of the valuations are made with its products.
The other firms that compete in the field of assessment tools and elaboration of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data supplied by manufacturers is far from easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Audatex’s commercial director, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with the information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, to the point that more versions, variants and motorizations have been released in the last five years than in the previous fifteen.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, these companies get to work.
It is a very difficult task, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and introduce its price.
In addition, each model is made a graphic image "smart" where you can "pin" different parts of tourism.
If it’s a mass-market model, the job can be done in a week if the process goes too fast.
If it is a minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models have information about Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile park that circulates, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the work of documentation and the elaboration of the databases, Audatex has eight centers spread around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually experts in mechanics) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
